President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Lana J. Marks as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to South Africa. Lana J. Marks is the founder and CEO of Lana Marks Ltd., Inc., a luxury fashion accessories producer. She has also served on the Women’s Leadership Board at the Harvard Kennedy School and the Women’s International Forum for over a decade.

Daniel B. Maffei has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Maritime Commission for the remainder of a five-year term expiring June 30, 2022. He is currently a Professor of Practice at the George Washington University Graduate School of Political Management and has previously served on the Federal Maritime Commission and in Congress representing portions of upstate New York.

L. E. Sola has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Maritime Commission for the remainder of a five-year term expiring June 30, 2023. He currently serves on the Florida Board of Pilots Commissioners and has previous experience as a Senior Sales Executive with Campers & Nicholson International and as a consultant with Arden & Price.

President Donald J. Trump has also announced his intention to nominate Robert A. Mandell and Don Munce as Members of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting for the remainder of six-year terms expiring January 31, 2022.

Additionally, Major General Jeffrey L. Milhorn has been appointed as a Member of the Interstate Commission on the Potomac River Basin.